Hi both,

Fieldwork closed yesterday. 1,070 completes, clean data file exported this morning.

A few notes on variables that came up during QA:

1. cooking_enjoyment: measured on a 5-point scale from 1 ("dislikes cooking") to 5 ("always_cook_from_scratch"). Distribution is roughly normal, peak at 3 ("cooks when convenient").

2. frm_brand_awareness: binary (yes/no) per brand. Captures aided awareness — "Have you heard of [brand]?" Shows recall after being shown the brand name, not spontaneous.

3. frm_brand_consideration: also binary. "Would you consider buying [brand]?" — strictly post-awareness filter.

4. N_Home_Cooking_per_week: integer, self-reported. Range 0-14. Median is 4.

5. The channel variable captures where respondents last purchased frozen ready meals. Top channels: Tesco (28%), Sainsbury's (19%), Asda (14%), frozen_food_specialist_eg_farmfoods (8%).

6. Gender split: 51% female, 49% male. Age distribution peaks at 35-44 (23%) and 45-54 (22%).

7. Income brackets run from below_20000 up to 150000_or_more. The 80000_to_149999 bracket has 28% of respondents — largest single bracket.

One issue: 12 respondents had missing data on annual_hh_income. We coded them as "prefer_not_to_answer" rather than dropping. This affects sample_base for income-filtered queries.

Data file is on the shared drive. Let me know if you need anything re-cut.

Laura
